"type":"p",
"hlId":"d67404",
"children":[
"A 68-year-old man is hospitalized following a seizure. Symptoms of fever, chills, dark urine, and headache began when he returned from a 3-week trip to Malaysia, Laos, and Cambodia. He is adherent to a mefloquine chemoprophylactic malaria regimen. Medical history is significant for splenectomy at age 12 years following a bicycle accident. He takes no other medications."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ec3671",
"children":[
"On physical examination, the patient is confused. Temperature is 39.8 °C (103.6 °F), blood pressure is 92/58 mm Hg, pulse rate is 92/min, and respiration rate is 20/min. Neurologic examination is nonfocal. Cardiopulmonary examination reveals crackles at the lung bases."
]
},
